claim.claim-text:
The detection device as claimed in claim 2, wherein

the circulation exercise device (21) comprises a gear (22) having n salients as the light blockers (211), multiple notches as the breaches (212) and a crank (25) mounted on the gear (22);

the controller (122) defines a serial number pk to each signal combination and estimates the angle θ° of the crank (25) and rotation speed RPM of the gear (22), wherein θ°=pk*360⁢°n; RPM=60sT⁢1;

T1: a duration of time in which the gear (22) finishes a complete revolution.

The detection device as claimed in claim 3, wherein

the state detector (11) further comprises an aperture sensor (113) mounted on the circuit board (110), located at a circular motion trace of an aperture (220) formed on the gear (22) and detecting the aperture (220) to generate a zeroization signal;

the controller (122) is electrically connected to the aperture sensor (113) and regards the zeroization signal as an initial point for defining the serial numbers pk.

The monitoring system as claimed in claim 10, wherein

the circulation exercise device (21) comprises a gear (22) having n salients as the light blockers (211), multiple notches as the breaches (212) and a crank (25) mounted on the gear (22);

the controller (122) defines a serial number pk to each signal combination and estimates the angle θ° of the crank (25) and rotation speed RPM of the gear (22), wherein θ°=pk*360⁢°n; RPM=60sT⁢1;

T1: a duration of time in which the gear (22) finishes a complete revolution.
